      • getRegistrationToken

        void getRegistrationToken(java.lang.String assetId,
                          java.lang.String uid,
                          java.lang.String type,
                          java.lang.String timeZone,
                          java.lang.String deviceUUID,
                          ResultListener<com.tuya.iotapp.activator.bean.RegistrationTokenBean> listener)

        Returns a device pairing token.

        Parameters:
        assetId - The asset ID to which the device will be bound.
        uid - The value of uid to which the device will be bound.
        type - The type of device pairing.
        timeZone - The time zone ID of String type. You can get the value from IotCommonUtil in Swift and from NSTimeZone in Objective-C.
        deviceUUID - Required when the type of device pairing is set to Bluetooth Low Energy (Bluetooth LE).
        listener - Called when the task is finished and the value of RegistrationTokenBean is returned. Otherwise, an error message is returned.

      • getRegistrationResultToken

        void getRegistrationResultToken(java.lang.String token,
                                ResultListener<com.tuya.iotapp.activator.bean.DeviceRegistrationResultBean> listener)

        Runs the polling task to check the device pairing result. Device pairing is an asynchronous process. The time when a device is paired depends on the network quality. You must make the API request to check the device pairing result. The polling task is stopped when a list of paired devices is returned or when the pairing task timed out.

        The polling task is run once per second. The timeout value of the pairing task is recommended to be 100 seconds.

        Parameters:
        token - The device pairing token.
        listener - Called when the task is finished and the paired devices with DeviceRegistrationResultBean are returned. Otherwise, an error message is returned.

                  java.lang.String timeZoneId,
                  ResultListener<java.lang.String> listener)

        Pairs a narrowband (NB) device by scanning a QR code.

        Parameters:
        qrcode - The result of scanning the QR code.
        assetId - The asset ID to which the specified device will be bound.
        timeZoneId - The ID of the time zone to which the device belongs.
        listener - Called when the task is finished and the paired device is returned. Otherwise, an error message is returned.

      • queryRegistrationGateways

        Parameters:

        listener - Called when the task is finished and the bound gateways are returned. Otherwise, an error message is returned.

      • discoverSubDevices

        void discoverSubDevices(java.lang.String deviceId,
                        int duration,
                        ResultListener<java.lang.Boolean> listener)

        Enables a specific gateway device to scan for unpaired sub-devices.

        Parameters:
        deviceId - The ID of the gateway device.
        duration - The scanning duration of the gateway. Unit: seconds. Valid values: 0 to 3600. Default value: 100. To disable scanning, set the value to 0.
        listener - Called when the task is finished and the true value is returned. Otherwise, the false value is returned.

      • querySubDeviceRegistrationResult

        void querySubDeviceRegistrationResult(java.lang.String deviceId,
                                      long discoveryTime,
                                      ResultListener<java.util.List> listener)

        Returns the sub-devices that have been paired with a specific device after the specified start time.

        Parameters:
        deviceId - The ID of the gateway device.
        discoveryTime - The start time of the period in which the specified gateway has scanned for devices.
        listener - Called when the task is finished and the paired sub-devices are returned. Otherwise, an error message is returned.
